279
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,559
You're afraid that if you love someone,

280
00:27:18,119 --> 00:27:20,279
you'll lose them.

281
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,319
What happened at the mall…

282
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:34,119
You were hesitant to enter

283
00:27:36,839 --> 00:27:39,119
not because of bad memories,

284
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:47,319
but because it's where you lost
your loved one.

285
00:27:49,119 --> 00:27:51,200
You lost him for good.

286
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:13,559
I never realized that my backstory

287
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:17,200
had everyone upset.

288
00:28:21,519 --> 00:28:24,880
This must be why he loved to hug me

289
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:28,079
when he was sad.

290
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,799
It wasn't because he loved the teddy bear,

291
00:28:34,559 --> 00:28:35,720
but because

292
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:39,480
I represented someone he loved dearly.

293
00:28:43,839 --> 00:28:45,559
I apologize for my lies.

294
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,519
I am actually hurt

295
00:28:50,559 --> 00:28:52,400
and jealous of Tatarn.

296
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,359
Am I a liar now?

297
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,680
But no matter how jealous I am,

298
00:29:05,839 --> 00:29:07,480
I'll always be here.

299
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:11,000
Whatever reason he had for hugging me,

300
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:13,720
his hugs

301
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,000
have always been my safe harbor.

302
00:29:25,799 --> 00:29:28,640
Right now, he's in need
of a safe harbor too,

303
00:29:31,319 --> 00:29:32,480
isn't he?

304
00:30:00,319 --> 00:30:03,680
What can I do to help
Nut and his mom reconcile?

305
00:30:04,319 --> 00:30:08,160
At first, you two fought.
Now, Nut and his mom also have issues.

306
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,160
If you won't help, be quiet.

307
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,319
Nut and his mom
have always been like this.

308
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,799
We've spoken about it.

309
00:30:17,079 --> 00:30:18,440
But…

310
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,680
as you know,

311
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,240
he's a complex character.

312
00:30:23,319 --> 00:30:25,519
He has been through a lot.

313
00:30:26,839 --> 00:30:28,119
Right now,

314
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,720
he has a good person supporting him.

315
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,960
I think things are looking better.

316
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:38,039
They are a family. They'll talk it out.

317
00:30:38,119 --> 00:30:40,039
Someone once told me,

318
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:43,039
to help another person understand,

319
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,039
you should be honest.

320
00:30:46,079 --> 00:30:48,079
Talking is not that hard.

321
00:30:48,799 --> 00:30:50,039
I'll give it a try.

322
00:30:51,079 --> 00:30:53,119
That lot is now working things out.

323
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,119
This lot needs to do the same.

324
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,759
What's with that lot and this lot?

325
00:30:56,839 --> 00:30:59,119
I'm not talking to you.

326
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:01,599
I have something important to discuss.

327
00:31:03,519 --> 00:31:04,720
Tomorrow,

328
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:06,920
will you meet me?

329
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,279
I have something important to discuss.

330
00:31:23,759 --> 00:31:24,920
Tomorrow,

331
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,160
will you meet me?

332
00:31:47,039 --> 00:31:47,960
Hey.

333
00:33:21,759 --> 00:33:22,880
What are you thinking?

334
00:33:24,319 --> 00:33:25,400
Nothing.

335
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:34,680
If you want me to do that,

336
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:37,319
let me in first.

337
00:33:40,359 --> 00:33:41,839
Just say what you have to say,

338
00:33:42,319 --> 00:33:43,880
so I can go back to bed.

339
00:33:44,599 --> 00:33:46,279
Why did you want to see me so early?

340
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:49,559
Let me ask you this.

341
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:53,359
Do you not like younger guys,
or do you just not like me?

342
00:33:57,759 --> 00:33:59,680
You seem to like me, though.

343
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:03,079
Why do you pretend
that you have no feelings?

344
00:34:03,839 --> 00:34:04,920
What's wrong?

345
00:34:08,519 --> 00:34:11,639
I want to know what I have to do
for you to give me a chance.

346
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:13,239
Could it be

347
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:14,840
that whatever I do,

348
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,239
you're never going to like me

349
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,599
because you can't forget your damn ex?

350
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:22,280
Come on.

351
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,119
I'm being serious.

352
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:30,559
Not every kid is like that.

353
00:34:31,039 --> 00:34:33,679
There are many good kids out there.

354
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,679
You don't have to come.

355
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:39,159
It's just a scratch. It's not deadly.

356
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,639
Once I get my salary,

357
00:34:44,119 --> 00:34:45,639
I'll treat you to a meal.

358
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:47,440
It's just tiring

359
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,719
when you try your best to please someone,

360
00:34:51,239 --> 00:34:52,480
but they don't even notice.

361
00:34:58,559 --> 00:35:00,280
Why aren't you saying anything?

362
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,760
You're making me nervous.

363
00:35:07,199 --> 00:35:08,360
Gen?

364
00:35:10,559 --> 00:35:11,840
Is it you, Gen?

365
00:35:14,719 --> 00:35:16,199
Win.

366
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,000
When did you get back from Australia?

367
00:35:28,079 --> 00:35:29,719
A month ago.

368
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:34,679
May I ask

369
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:37,599
who you prepared this surprise for?

370
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:39,880
Your boyfriend?

371
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:43,440
Yes. We met when we were there.

372
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,079
We came back together.

373
00:35:46,039 --> 00:35:48,159
I wanted to make it official.

374
00:35:51,519 --> 00:35:53,519
You and I haven't spoken for three years.

375
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:55,679
I'm glad

376
00:35:56,159 --> 00:35:57,679
that we can still talk.

377
00:36:00,199 --> 00:36:01,360
Well,

378
00:36:02,079 --> 00:36:03,280
we parted on good terms.

379
00:36:04,239 --> 00:36:05,679
Even though I was upset,

380
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:07,639
I understood

381
00:36:09,119 --> 00:36:10,840
that you had to plan for your future.

382
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:14,679
Back then, I didn't treat you well,

383
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:18,000
but you always treated me like a king.

384
00:36:22,039 --> 00:36:23,039
Actually,

385
00:36:23,519 --> 00:36:24,960
I did many things for you

386
00:36:25,639 --> 00:36:27,199
without you having to ask.

387
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:28,920
You were head over heels.

388
00:36:32,159 --> 00:36:33,320
Seriously though,

389
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,599
if I could turn back time,

390
00:36:35,679 --> 00:36:37,519
I would still break up with you.

391
00:36:38,559 --> 00:36:39,880
Good relationships

392
00:36:40,719 --> 00:36:42,400
come at the right time.

393
00:36:47,199 --> 00:36:48,519
-Song…
-By the way.

394
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:50,199
What is it?

395
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,400
I'm all grown up now.

396
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:53,400
I eat my vegetables,

397
00:36:55,199 --> 00:36:56,760
but I no longer like cabbage.

398
00:36:57,840 --> 00:36:59,360
Do you still grow it?

399
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,760
No, I don't grow it anymore.

400
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:04,800
I grow ivy gourd now, got it?

401
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,280
I thought you had left.

402
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:31,280
I can wait.

403
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,280
I just don't want to watch.

404
00:37:34,599 --> 00:37:37,320
You're too sensitive.
It's because you're the youngest son.

405
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,400
What did cabbage boy want?

406
00:37:43,159 --> 00:37:44,559
His name is Marvin.

407
00:37:44,639 --> 00:37:46,000
I don't care what his name is.

408
00:37:46,519 --> 00:37:49,840
Tell me what you were talking about.
Are you getting back together?

409
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:52,519
Song, are you blind?

410
00:37:52,599 --> 00:37:54,119
This is for his boyfriend.

411
00:37:54,199 --> 00:37:56,239
Where would I fit in?

412
00:38:02,679 --> 00:38:04,800
You didn't answer my question.

413
00:38:09,519 --> 00:38:11,880
Did you have to drag me here
to tell me your answer?

414
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:16,159
I want to talk this through.

415
00:38:16,239 --> 00:38:17,719
Here.

416
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:20,840
Drink this to cool yourself down
and listen to me.

417
00:38:21,679 --> 00:38:22,519
Okay?

418
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:24,639
Okay.

419
00:38:26,119 --> 00:38:29,079
You've talked with your ex.
Now, you have to talk to the new guy.

420
00:38:34,159 --> 00:38:35,679
Why do you keep resisting me?

421
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:39,719
Why? Did cabbage boy hurt you that badly?

422
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:43,440
We were in a relationship three years ago.

423
00:38:44,119 --> 00:38:45,599
He was 18 at the time.

424
00:38:46,159 --> 00:38:47,199
I was 24.

425
00:38:49,079 --> 00:38:50,239
Did he ask you out?

426
00:38:51,159 --> 00:38:52,960
No, I approached him.

427
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,320
He was so cute.

428
00:38:59,159 --> 00:39:01,039
I was generous with my money.

429
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:04,800
He liked eating cabbage, so I grew some.

430
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,880
I even cooked it for him.

431
00:39:14,400 --> 00:39:15,840
It lasted less than a year.

432
00:39:17,599 --> 00:39:18,960
He went abroad to study.

433
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:23,199
I told him I was willing to wait,

434
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:25,599
but he said I shouldn't waste my time.

435
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:28,599
Also, he might meet someone better.

436
00:39:31,039 --> 00:39:32,760
When I saw him just now,

437
00:39:33,719 --> 00:39:35,440
he stood by what he said before

438
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:40,239
and he's not sorry he said it.

439
00:39:45,039 --> 00:39:47,000
Maybe he was focusing on his future,

440
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:50,679
but he obviously didn't love you enough.

441
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,199
That's why he let you go.

442
00:39:53,239 --> 00:39:55,400
He and I are different people, you know?

443
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,639
I know that.

444
00:39:56,719 --> 00:39:58,119
What are you afraid of then?

445
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:03,440
What happened to you in the past

446
00:40:04,039 --> 00:40:05,599
made you lose faith in love,

447
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:11,800
but I'm going to show you
how serious I am about you.

448
00:40:19,119 --> 00:40:20,599
People change.

449
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,159
You're young. You have a lot to see.

450
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:27,000
This is all I have to say.

451
00:40:29,079 --> 00:40:30,039
Hey.

452
00:40:30,119 --> 00:40:32,480
Hey, where are you going?

453
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:36,960
Hey.

454
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:38,639
So what if I'm young?

455
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,039
I'll grow up one day.

456
00:40:44,559 --> 00:40:47,079
You're afraid I'll change,
but what about you?

457
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:50,199
If you were to die tomorrow,
what would I do?

458
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,320
Are you cursing me?

459
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:53,079
I'm not cursing you.

460
00:40:53,679 --> 00:40:54,599
I'm serious.

461
00:40:56,480 --> 00:41:00,199
What are you afraid of? It just
complicates everything and wastes time.

462
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:02,480
We don't know what will happen tomorrow.

463
00:41:03,039 --> 00:41:05,119
Why can't we just get together now?

464
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:20,039
Where are you going?

465
00:41:20,119 --> 00:41:22,559
Can we talk this through?

466
00:41:23,599 --> 00:41:25,360
Wait.

467
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:26,719
I'm going home.

468
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:33,800
I need to water my plant,

469
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,000
so it grows quickly,

470
00:41:35,079 --> 00:41:36,000
like someone I know.

471
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:47,960
Are you agreeing to our relationship?

472
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:50,679
Finally!

473
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,679
I can't wait to eat some ivy gourd leaves.

474
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:55,119
-Hooray.
-Let me down.

475
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:59,239
We're in a park. Don't make so much noise.

476
00:41:59,320 --> 00:42:00,880
I'll refrain from making noise.

477
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:03,159
-Let me kiss you instead.
-Don't.

478
00:42:03,239 --> 00:42:07,039
Stop it. Keep your hands to yourself.
Do you hear me?

479
00:42:07,119 --> 00:42:09,679
Look, there are people around.

480
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,400
Okay?

481
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,280
I love you. Let's go home, shall we?

482
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:17,119
Come on.

483
00:42:17,199 --> 00:42:18,480
-Are you driving me?
-Yes.

484
00:42:18,559 --> 00:42:21,119
Get on my back.

485
00:42:21,639 --> 00:42:22,599
One, two, three.

486
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:24,639
Let's go home.

487
00:42:37,119 --> 00:42:38,480
Let me help you.

488
00:42:43,960 --> 00:42:45,719
Are you thinking about last night?

489
00:42:47,679 --> 00:42:49,440
Why would I?

490
00:42:51,079 --> 00:42:54,320
You want to make things better, don't you?

491
00:42:55,960 --> 00:42:57,639
You get irritable with your mom,

492
00:42:58,519 --> 00:43:00,000
but you're not really angry.

493
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:03,079
You just…

494
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:05,039
hold a grudge.

495
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:08,639
You've been holding onto it for so long

496
00:43:09,599 --> 00:43:11,519
and you can't seem to let it go, right?

497
00:43:13,159 --> 00:43:14,599
You're such a know-it-all.

498
00:43:15,559 --> 00:43:17,320
Someone once told me

499
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:20,639
that families should try
to resolve their problems.

500
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:23,719
If you love someone, you should say so.

501
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:27,840
If you want to understand,
you should talk to each other.

502
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:29,960
Mutual understanding

503
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:32,360
requires an open mind.

504
00:43:33,239 --> 00:43:35,119
When did you get so smart?

505
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:37,840
Do you like it?

506
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:40,119
I like it.

507
00:43:40,599 --> 00:43:42,039
I like listening to your voice.

508
00:43:47,559 --> 00:43:48,599
Let me help.

509
00:44:10,599 --> 00:44:12,360
Don't do what you did yesterday.

510
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,079
As long as Mom doesn't start it.

511
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:18,320
Nut.

512
00:44:21,679 --> 00:44:23,719
All right. I won't.

513
00:44:24,679 --> 00:44:25,840
Are you satisfied now?

514
00:44:27,239 --> 00:44:28,400
I'm satisfied.

515
00:44:29,159 --> 00:44:30,960
You're very cute like this.

516
00:44:31,880 --> 00:44:33,480
If I'm cute, I want a reward.

517
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:53,960
Let me think about what to give you.

518
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:01,079
Kuenchai.

519
00:45:13,639 --> 00:45:14,840
Mrs. Na.

520
00:45:17,719 --> 00:45:18,639
Mom.

521
00:45:21,239 --> 00:45:22,360
I'll check upstairs.

522
00:45:25,599 --> 00:45:26,679
Mom.

523
00:45:33,239 --> 00:45:36,079
Sorry, the number you've dialed
cannot be reached--

524
00:45:36,159 --> 00:45:37,760
She's not upstairs.

525
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:40,320
Sorry--

526
00:45:40,400 --> 00:45:42,840
Where did she go?
Why is her phone switched off?

527
00:45:45,519 --> 00:45:46,920
I forgot to tell you

528
00:45:47,480 --> 00:45:49,119
that her phone is broken.

529
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:54,360
I'll go and ask the neighbors.

530
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:08,239
Ms. Chair, do you know where Mrs. Na went?

531
00:46:11,519 --> 00:46:12,840
Ms. Chair.

532
00:46:17,280 --> 00:46:18,719
Ms. Chair.

533
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:20,760
Ms. Chair.

534
00:46:29,639 --> 00:46:31,599
Chu and Nhong didn't see anything.

535
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:46,480
Kuenchai.

536
00:46:56,280 --> 00:46:57,679
I have a doctor's appointment.

537
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:00,800
I'm going to see the doctor.

538
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:03,480
She is…

539
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,920
I forgot your mom
had an appointment this month.

540
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:25,079
I'm sorry for not taking good care of her.

541
00:47:25,559 --> 00:47:28,199
It's not your fault. It's my fault.

542
00:47:28,960 --> 00:47:31,159
You're worried about her too, aren't you?

543
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,159
-Hi, there.
-Hello.

544
00:47:33,239 --> 00:47:34,800
Hi, Nut, Tofu.

545
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:35,960
I came to pick Mom up.

546
00:47:36,559 --> 00:47:37,840
Really?

547
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:41,679
I saw her going that way.

548
00:47:44,159 --> 00:47:46,159
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

549
00:47:56,039 --> 00:47:59,119
The psychiatrist sent me
the preliminary test results.

550
00:47:59,679 --> 00:48:01,000
You shouldn't worry.

551
00:48:01,519 --> 00:48:05,559
The symptoms you described
could have stemmed from several causes.

552
00:48:05,639 --> 00:48:08,960
It could be a side effect of the medicine.

553
00:48:09,039 --> 00:48:10,320
How about this?

554
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:12,559
I'm going to run a few more tests

555
00:48:12,639 --> 00:48:15,519
and do an additional blood test.

556
00:48:15,599 --> 00:48:18,320
This way we can identify the real cause.

557
00:48:54,280 --> 00:48:55,360
There she is.

558
