ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE

682
00:58:38,719 --> 00:58:42,599
WHAT IS ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE?

683
00:59:42,679 --> 00:59:44,800
Ms. Chair has fallen asleep.

684
00:59:46,960 --> 00:59:48,679
The house is really quiet.

685
00:59:49,760 --> 00:59:51,400
Mrs. Na has been very quiet too.

686
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:55,800
Surely, she's still upset
about what happened last night.

687
00:59:56,639 --> 00:59:58,920
I think there's more to it.

688
01:00:01,239 --> 01:00:03,679
Since we came back from the hospital,

689
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:05,960
she has been silent,

690
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:08,639
as if she has something on her mind.

691
01:00:14,320 --> 01:00:15,440
Tofu?

692
01:00:24,159 --> 01:00:25,639
Can you do me a favor?

693
01:00:36,280 --> 01:00:38,280
I know that doing this is wrong.

694
01:00:39,800 --> 01:00:42,280
If Nut finds out, he'll be angry with me.

695
01:00:43,000 --> 01:00:45,360
I want to know what he thinks about me.

696
01:00:46,599 --> 01:00:47,679
I want to know

697
01:00:49,079 --> 01:00:50,920
if he says anything bad about me.

698
01:00:53,480 --> 01:00:55,559
Why do you want to find out
all of a sudden?

699
01:00:56,519 --> 01:00:59,280
Is it because of last night?

700
01:01:01,760 --> 01:01:04,159
I made many mistakes in the past.

701
01:01:05,159 --> 01:01:07,480
I want to find a way to correct them.

702
01:01:10,239 --> 01:01:12,480
I want to make things better

703
01:01:13,119 --> 01:01:14,800
before…

704
01:01:16,960 --> 01:01:19,079
it's too late.

705
01:01:20,920 --> 01:01:23,000
Can you read it out for me?

706
01:01:24,920 --> 01:01:26,119
Okay.

707
01:01:37,440 --> 01:01:38,639
Moving house

708
01:01:39,119 --> 01:01:40,960
is such a hassle.

709
01:01:46,360 --> 01:01:48,360
There are so many things to think about.

710
01:01:49,039 --> 01:01:52,559
There's the house itself
and the people in it.

711
01:01:53,880 --> 01:01:57,519
At least, living here is better
than our old place.

712
01:02:04,760 --> 01:02:06,800
I haven't bought everything we need yet.

713
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:12,360
Fortunately, I brought my desk and chair
from our old house.

714
01:02:13,079 --> 01:02:14,639
They might be old,

715
01:02:15,559 --> 01:02:16,920
but I really like them.

716
01:02:19,039 --> 01:02:20,880
It's my favorite desk.

717
01:02:21,440 --> 01:02:23,480
I've written a lot on it.

718
01:02:25,039 --> 01:02:28,039
I like sitting at this desk while working.

719
01:02:29,320 --> 01:02:31,079
I feel comfortable writing on it.

720
01:02:33,239 --> 01:02:36,800
You used to tell me
that Nut wasn't home a lot.

721
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:40,119
But it sounds like he loves this house.

722
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:43,039
He chose everything in the house.

723
01:02:44,119 --> 01:02:45,760
I'm terrible.

724
01:02:46,840 --> 01:02:48,960
I've lived in this house for years,

725
01:02:51,280 --> 01:02:54,760
but I've never thought
about how each item came about.

726
01:02:56,559 --> 01:02:57,679
It's okay.

727
01:02:58,320 --> 01:02:59,679
It's just everyday stuff.

728
01:02:59,760 --> 01:03:01,599
But Nut's everyday thoughts

729
01:03:03,719 --> 01:03:05,400
don't seem to include me.

730
01:03:10,639 --> 01:03:11,880
I'm sure they do.

731
01:03:12,599 --> 01:03:14,360
I haven't reached halfway yet.

732
01:03:25,559 --> 01:03:26,519
Here we go.

733
01:03:30,239 --> 01:03:32,719
Mom's phone is so old.

734
01:03:33,239 --> 01:03:37,280
I'm getting my paycheck today.
I'll buy her a new phone.

735
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:41,360
I shouldn't have bought it.

736
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:44,760
She complained it was expensive.

737
01:03:44,840 --> 01:03:45,920
What's the matter?

738
01:03:47,239 --> 01:03:48,800
What else did he write?

739
01:03:51,960 --> 01:03:55,599
He wrote that you complained
it was expensive.

740
01:04:11,920 --> 01:04:15,719
I don't need something
this new and expensive.

741
01:04:15,800 --> 01:04:17,760
You should have saved the money.

742
01:04:29,559 --> 01:04:31,239
I didn't know what to do.

743
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:34,280
I didn't mean to be insensitive.

744
01:04:37,440 --> 01:04:40,199
I should have told him how good it felt

745
01:04:41,159 --> 01:04:43,440
that he had thought of me.

746
01:04:44,440 --> 01:04:47,920
I should have at least said thank you.

747
01:04:50,039 --> 01:04:51,920
But I didn't say that.

748
01:04:53,760 --> 01:04:56,559
Nut wanted you to have a good phone,

749
01:04:57,559 --> 01:05:01,159
while you wanted him
to keep the money for himself.

750
01:05:01,920 --> 01:05:04,039
You both had different ways

751
01:05:04,119 --> 01:05:05,800
of showing good intentions.

752
01:05:06,400 --> 01:05:08,840
If you had been honest
with each other that day,

753
01:05:09,760 --> 01:05:11,480
Nut wouldn't have been upset.

754
01:05:18,880 --> 01:05:20,599
What else did he write?

755
01:05:21,719 --> 01:05:22,960
There's more.

756
01:05:24,760 --> 01:05:26,880
I've already bought
everything for the house,

757
01:05:27,440 --> 01:05:29,400
but it's still so damn quiet.

758
01:05:30,519 --> 01:05:33,199
Adding a new member to the household

759
01:05:33,679 --> 01:05:35,320
should make it feel more like home.

760
01:05:40,719 --> 01:05:44,400
And this little guy is supposedly smart

761
01:05:44,480 --> 01:05:47,199
and easy to keep and train.

762
01:05:47,920 --> 01:05:49,519
He makes a good companion.

763
01:05:50,079 --> 01:05:52,000
He's just right for Mom.

764
01:05:52,079 --> 01:05:54,840
He can keep Mom company while I'm at work.

765
01:06:02,119 --> 01:06:03,800
Despite having heavy workload

766
01:06:04,599 --> 01:06:06,639
that makes him unable
to stay home with you,

767
01:06:06,719 --> 01:06:09,039
Nut is always trying to take care of you.

768
01:06:14,039 --> 01:06:15,679
I'm very lucky.

769
01:06:17,639 --> 01:06:19,320
He might be stubborn at times,

770
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:22,719
but he has always been a good son.

771
01:06:38,800 --> 01:06:40,239
I know now

772
01:06:41,079 --> 01:06:42,920
why she didn't want to read it herself.

773
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,880
She would rather not face
the harsh reality.

774
01:06:49,360 --> 01:06:50,559
The reality

775
01:06:51,719 --> 01:06:53,960
that Nut hardly ever writes about her.

776
01:06:55,639 --> 01:06:57,079
When he writes about her,

777
01:06:58,639 --> 01:07:00,639
it's not necessarily in a good light.

778
01:07:00,719 --> 01:07:03,400
You've done your best, Teddy.

779
01:07:03,480 --> 01:07:08,639
Sometimes, humans tell white lies
to make others feel better.

780
01:07:10,079 --> 01:07:12,239
I wasn't intending to lie to her.

781
01:07:13,239 --> 01:07:14,760
I know

782
01:07:15,760 --> 01:07:17,760
that even when he writes about her
that way,

783
01:07:18,880 --> 01:07:20,880
when it comes down to it, he loves her.

784
01:07:38,920 --> 01:07:41,159
If the mother protects her son
by hurting him,

785
01:07:41,239 --> 01:07:43,039
how does she expect him to understand?

786
01:07:43,639 --> 01:07:44,960
That's hard to say.

787
01:07:45,440 --> 01:07:49,880
There's more to what she did
than I can get from the script.

788
01:07:51,800 --> 01:07:55,400
It's not easy to tell
without scratching the surface.

789
01:08:04,199 --> 01:08:06,559
If you don't see us when you get home,
don't panic.

790
01:08:07,119 --> 01:08:10,320
I'm taking your mom out for some exercise
as Dr. Kanya recommended.

791
01:08:20,119 --> 01:08:22,039
Since I moved here,

792
01:08:22,119 --> 01:08:24,039
I've never come out for a walk like this.

793
01:08:25,039 --> 01:08:29,319
As a matter of fact,
I haven't done it since I was a kid.

794
01:08:29,399 --> 01:08:33,159
Back when I was still single,
I was a workaholic.

795
01:08:34,159 --> 01:08:38,399
When I got home, I had to look after
my mom who was old.

796
01:08:41,399 --> 01:08:43,359
After I got married,

797
01:08:44,039 --> 01:08:45,800
I had to take care of the family.

798
01:08:55,279 --> 01:08:57,880
You always put others' needs
before your own.

799
01:09:01,039 --> 01:09:02,600
I grew up with my mom.

800
01:09:03,279 --> 01:09:04,920
My parents separated.

801
01:09:06,479 --> 01:09:09,039
It really affected my mom.

802
01:09:11,279 --> 01:09:14,119
I just wanted to be good
to relieve her burden.

803
01:09:16,479 --> 01:09:18,119
When I got married,

804
01:09:20,399 --> 01:09:22,960
I wanted my children
to have a loving family.

805
01:09:23,479 --> 01:09:24,680
Not like mine.

806
01:09:28,199 --> 01:09:30,279
But Nut wasn't like other boys.

807
01:09:34,640 --> 01:09:35,960
Isn't this pretty?

808
01:09:36,479 --> 01:09:40,239
Nut. That's a girl's dress.
You can't wear that.

809
01:09:42,600 --> 01:09:43,560
Why not?

810
01:09:44,039 --> 01:09:47,199
Can't boys wear it? I like this dress.

811
01:09:49,720 --> 01:09:52,640
Pink is for girls.

812
01:09:52,720 --> 01:09:55,680
You are a boy.
You shouldn't like pastel rainbows.

813
01:09:56,239 --> 01:09:57,319
It's silly.

814
01:10:04,239 --> 01:10:07,439
Being different
isn't the same as being bad.

815
01:10:08,920 --> 01:10:11,199
I admit that I was negligent back then.

816
01:10:12,239 --> 01:10:16,079
I didn't know why Nut was like that.

817
01:10:17,880 --> 01:10:20,119
I was genuinely concerned.

818
01:10:21,119 --> 01:10:24,159
I was concerned about his future.

819
01:10:24,760 --> 01:10:26,399
I wondered if he would be accepted,

820
01:10:28,520 --> 01:10:30,600
if anyone would love him.

821
01:10:33,680 --> 01:10:35,560
His dad couldn't accept it

822
01:10:36,640 --> 01:10:40,479
and blamed me
for not raising him properly.

823
01:10:41,880 --> 01:10:43,600
That's why I took his dad's side

824
01:10:44,720 --> 01:10:46,960
and forbade Nut from being himself.

825
01:10:48,600 --> 01:10:51,359
He's turning gay
because of your negligence.

826
01:10:51,439 --> 01:10:52,680
He's just a nice boy.

827
01:10:52,760 --> 01:10:54,359
Don't talk back to me.

828
01:10:54,439 --> 01:10:56,319
Boys have to be strong.

829
01:10:56,399 --> 01:10:58,960
What kind of mom are you?

830
01:10:59,039 --> 01:11:00,399
I'm not taking it.

831
01:11:01,560 --> 01:11:03,279
I don't want to be a soldier.

832
01:11:03,760 --> 01:11:06,199
If you won't be a soldier,
what do you want to be?

833
01:11:06,680 --> 01:11:07,880
Anything.

834
01:11:08,439 --> 01:11:10,319
I just don't want to be like Dad.

835
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:13,159
Will you please

836
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:17,239
listen to your dad?

837
01:11:17,319 --> 01:11:18,640
He wants the best for you.

838
01:11:19,880 --> 01:11:20,960
He wants the best?

839
01:11:22,560 --> 01:11:26,119
For me or himself?

840
01:11:27,359 --> 01:11:29,640
I was weak and selfish.

841
01:11:32,279 --> 01:11:33,800
As a mother,

842
01:11:33,880 --> 01:11:35,359
I should have sided with him

843
01:11:37,000 --> 01:11:38,920
and protected him.

844
01:11:40,359 --> 01:11:42,720
Instead, I trampled on his heart.

845
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:48,000
I forced him to comply the way I did.

846
01:11:54,560 --> 01:11:56,600
I forbade him from being himself.

847
01:12:01,039 --> 01:12:03,600
I failed to support him.

848
01:12:19,720 --> 01:12:21,399
I know that you feel bad about it.

849
01:12:25,399 --> 01:12:27,640
But now that you've acknowledged
what happened,

850
01:12:29,640 --> 01:12:32,039
you feel better, don't you?

851
01:12:36,880 --> 01:12:38,920
If you want
to get anything off your chest,

852
01:12:40,239 --> 01:12:42,359
you can tell me.

853
01:12:43,680 --> 01:12:45,159
I'm willing to listen.

854
01:12:54,239 --> 01:12:55,760
After that day,

855
01:12:56,439 --> 01:12:58,399
Nut avoided me.

856
01:13:00,439 --> 01:13:03,000
He barely uttered a word to me.

857
01:13:05,479 --> 01:13:07,960
I never had a chance to apologize to him.

858
01:13:13,560 --> 01:13:16,239
After his dad passed away,
we became even more distant.

859
01:13:24,920 --> 01:13:25,840
Nut.

860
01:13:26,560 --> 01:13:28,439
Come for dinner. I'll warm it up.

861
01:13:29,439 --> 01:13:31,720
There's no need. I've eaten.

862
01:13:47,479 --> 01:13:48,560
Mom,

863
01:13:49,119 --> 01:13:50,680
I'm moving to a dorm next week.

864
01:14:57,119 --> 01:14:59,920
I knew that Nut moved here
because of my condition.

865
01:15:00,920 --> 01:15:03,840
He didn't want me to be reminded
of what had happened before.

866
01:15:08,600 --> 01:15:10,239
Despite our move,

867
01:15:11,279 --> 01:15:14,399
the distance between us didn't change.

868
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:27,319
The longer it went on,

869
01:15:29,239 --> 01:15:32,720
the harder it became to heal the rift.

870
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:35,800
Then I came to realize

871
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:41,039
that Nut didn't need me anymore.

872
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:57,039
I wronged him

873
01:16:00,680 --> 01:16:03,960
because I grew up in an unstable family.

874
01:16:05,680 --> 01:16:08,760
I wished for my own family to be perfect.

875
01:16:10,520 --> 01:16:13,479
But in this world, nothing is perfect.

876
01:16:14,439 --> 01:16:16,359
I used to fear

877
01:16:18,199 --> 01:16:21,359
that Nut was abnormal for being like this.

878
01:16:22,439 --> 01:16:25,119
In fact, being gay is normal.

879
01:16:29,199 --> 01:16:30,680
These days

880
01:16:33,119 --> 01:16:34,960
seeing him all grown up,

881
01:16:35,680 --> 01:16:38,000
capable of supporting himself…

882
01:16:38,960 --> 01:16:42,520
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW
WITH PEERANUT BURARAT

883
01:16:57,680 --> 01:16:58,960
…being accepted by others,

884
01:16:59,800 --> 01:17:02,159
with friends like everyone else…

885
01:17:02,239 --> 01:17:04,079
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW
WITH PEERANUT BURARAT

886
01:17:20,039 --> 01:17:22,319
I've realized that kids
should be themselves.

887
01:17:24,119 --> 01:17:26,640
They should be allowed
to choose their own paths

888
01:17:28,079 --> 01:17:31,840
with the support of their parents,

889
01:17:32,880 --> 01:17:34,560
without being under control.

890
01:17:35,720 --> 01:17:37,920
A child's life is their own,

891
01:17:38,479 --> 01:17:40,199
not their parents'.

892
01:17:43,960 --> 01:17:46,680
You accepted who he was long ago, right?

893
01:17:48,920 --> 01:17:51,119
That's why you could accept me.

894
01:17:51,800 --> 01:17:55,119
I never wanted to kick you out
like Nut always feared.

895
01:17:56,359 --> 01:18:00,359
I'm actually thankful
for your presence in our life.

896
01:18:02,319 --> 01:18:04,720
I no longer care about
what others might say.

897
01:18:06,119 --> 01:18:07,640
The smile on his face

898
01:18:08,199 --> 01:18:10,920
makes me realize what makes him happy

899
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:13,840
and what makes me happy.

900
01:18:17,079 --> 01:18:20,960
Thank you
for throwing me a birthday party.

901
01:18:22,840 --> 01:18:23,960
Do you like it?

902
01:18:25,640 --> 01:18:26,479
Yes.

903
01:18:27,640 --> 01:18:29,079
Do you like the party

904
01:18:29,560 --> 01:18:31,119
or me?

905
01:18:33,720 --> 01:18:34,920
What a cheap shot.

906
01:18:37,720 --> 01:18:39,479
When you asked me what I wanted

907
01:18:39,560 --> 01:18:41,560
for my birthday

908
01:18:42,359 --> 01:18:43,960
and I said nothing,

909
01:18:48,359 --> 01:18:50,039
that's because

910
01:18:52,119 --> 01:18:53,640
I already have you.

911
01:18:59,520 --> 01:19:01,479
Stay by my side…

912
01:19:04,239 --> 01:19:05,760
and don't go anywhere.

913
01:19:15,000 --> 01:19:16,840
Thank you so much

914
01:19:18,119 --> 01:19:20,039
for making him happy.

915
01:19:22,359 --> 01:19:26,680
You make him laugh and smile
like I haven't seen him do for so long.

916
01:19:30,119 --> 01:19:31,479
Also,

917
01:19:33,720 --> 01:19:35,520
thank you…

918
01:19:38,359 --> 01:19:40,000
for being there for me

919
01:19:40,800 --> 01:19:43,359
and supporting me through all this.

920
01:19:48,600 --> 01:19:51,960
If I hadn't been sick, I would have
been able to talk to him more.

921
01:19:52,960 --> 01:19:56,159
Now that I feel better
and I'm thinking straight,

922
01:19:57,199 --> 01:19:58,880
it seems like it's too late.

923
01:20:00,840 --> 01:20:02,640
It's never too late.

924
01:20:05,039 --> 01:20:07,199
You can always start over.

925
01:20:08,279 --> 01:20:10,119
You can do that right this minute.

926
01:20:34,680 --> 01:20:35,840
Shall we go home?

927
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:38,920
Let's go.

928
01:21:22,199 --> 01:21:24,000
How about this?

929
01:21:24,479 --> 01:21:26,119
Think about it.

930
01:21:26,600 --> 01:21:28,199
From what you've written,

931
01:21:28,279 --> 01:21:29,960
the mother and her son

932
01:21:30,039 --> 01:21:32,000
don't really show it,

933
01:21:33,319 --> 01:21:34,760
but I can tell for sure

934
01:21:35,800 --> 01:21:37,319
that they still love each other.

935
01:21:40,920 --> 01:21:42,600
Do you think I should revise it?

936
01:21:43,159 --> 01:21:45,079
You should ask yourself that.

937
01:21:46,039 --> 01:21:48,560
You're the one writing it.

938
01:21:49,479 --> 01:21:52,880
How the relationship
between the mom and her son will turn out

939
01:21:53,560 --> 01:21:55,199
is not up to me.

940
01:21:56,079 --> 01:21:57,640
It's up to you.

941
01:22:54,920 --> 01:22:56,920
You came home late today, Nut.

942
01:22:59,720 --> 01:23:02,079
I thought we might go out for a walk.

943
01:23:02,760 --> 01:23:04,640
I took a walk with your mom.

944
01:23:04,720 --> 01:23:06,439
We talked about many things.

945
01:23:14,000 --> 01:23:16,119
She knows about us.

946
01:23:18,800 --> 01:23:20,680
She's not opposed to it.

947
01:23:23,800 --> 01:23:26,560
Perhaps she doesn't say anything,

948
01:23:27,600 --> 01:23:29,479
not because she doesn't care,

949
01:23:31,159 --> 01:23:33,920
but because she accepts who you are.

950
01:23:41,560 --> 01:23:42,880
I know

951
01:23:43,359 --> 01:23:44,960
that you're staying silent

952
01:23:45,439 --> 01:23:47,279
because you're thinking.

953
01:23:50,920 --> 01:23:52,840
Your mom is like this too.

954
01:23:54,279 --> 01:23:56,359
If you listen carefully,

955
01:23:57,159 --> 01:23:58,800
the silence

956
01:23:59,479 --> 01:24:02,479
may hide deep love and concern.

957
01:24:06,039 --> 01:24:09,560
Don't you think you should give yourself

958
01:24:10,520 --> 01:24:12,800
and give your mom a chance?

959
01:24:18,640 --> 01:24:20,079
You're quite the philosopher.

960
01:24:22,199 --> 01:24:23,399
Are you talking now?

961
01:24:28,720 --> 01:24:30,880
Today, your mom had sore feet.

962
01:24:32,279 --> 01:24:34,399
Shall we buy her new shoes tomorrow?

963
01:25:03,800 --> 01:25:04,960
Mrs. Na?

964
01:25:09,880 --> 01:25:13,159
I came to tell you to dress up tomorrow.

965
01:25:13,239 --> 01:25:14,119
Yes?

966
01:25:16,000 --> 01:25:16,880
Why?

967
01:25:16,960 --> 01:25:20,119
Well, we are going shopping tomorrow.

968
01:25:20,199 --> 01:25:21,399
Nut is taking us.

969
01:25:21,960 --> 01:25:22,880
Really?

970
01:26:13,039 --> 01:26:15,039
Is this outfit okay, Tofu?

971
01:26:16,880 --> 01:26:19,600
I don't go out much.
I only have old clothes.

972
01:26:20,760 --> 01:26:21,840
You look great.

973
01:26:24,239 --> 01:26:25,119
Where's Nut?

974
01:26:30,039 --> 01:26:30,960
He…

975
01:26:43,439 --> 01:26:46,239
Are they both your sons?
They're so handsome.

976
01:26:46,720 --> 01:26:47,720
Yes.

977
01:26:48,399 --> 01:26:49,720
He is my son.

978
01:26:51,079 --> 01:26:52,600
He is also my son.

979
01:26:54,960 --> 01:26:58,439
Tarn told me
that he wanted Nut to be happy,

980
01:26:59,399 --> 01:27:01,079
and what happened between them

981
01:27:01,760 --> 01:27:05,640
should just be left as a happy memory.

982
01:27:06,600 --> 01:27:09,079
He was the one who made me understand

983
01:27:09,159 --> 01:27:10,800
that being gay isn't a disease.

984
01:27:11,439 --> 01:27:12,760
It's not down to bad karma,

985
01:27:14,159 --> 01:27:15,640
or an emotional disorder.

986
01:27:16,359 --> 01:27:18,479
And it's not a joke.

987
